<script type="application/ld+json">
{"@context":"https://schema.org","@graph":[
{"@type":"MedicalWebPage","url":"https://rxmedcalc.com/medical-calculators/due-date","name":"Pregnancy Due Date Calculator India","description":"Calculate EDD from LMP, IVF transfer date, or ultrasound CRL. Current pregnancy week, trimester, Indian antenatal scan schedule.","inLanguage":"en","audience":{"@type":"MedicalAudience","audienceType":"Patient, Obstetrician, Gynaecologist, General Practitioner"},"dateModified":"2025-04-17"},
{"@type":"BreadcrumbList","itemListElement":[{"@type":"ListItem","position":1,"name":"Home","item":"https://rxmedcalc.com/"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":2,"name":"Calculators","item":"https://rxmedcalc.com/medical-calculators/"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":3,"name":"Due Date Calculator","item":"https://rxmedcalc.com/medical-calculators/due-date"}]},
{"@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[
{"@type":"Question","name":"How is the due date calculated from LMP?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Using Naegele's Rule: add 280 days (40 weeks) to the first day of the Last Menstrual Period (LMP), adjusted for cycle length. For a 28-day cycle this equals LMP + 9 months + 7 days. Our calculator automatically adjusts for cycle lengths of 21–45 days."}},
{"@type":"Question","name":"How accurate is the LMP method for due date?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The LMP method assumes a regular 28-day cycle with ovulation on day 14. It is accurate to within ±2 weeks. An early ultrasound (7–13 weeks, measuring CRL) is the gold standard and is accurate to ±5–7 days. If the ultrasound date differs from LMP by more than 7 days, obstetricians in India typically correct the EDD to the ultrasound-based date."}},
{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the due date for IVF Day 5 transfer?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"For a Day 5 blastocyst transfer, add 261 days to the transfer date. For a Day 3 embryo transfer, add 263 days. This is because the embryo is already 5 or 3 days old at transfer, so fewer days are added to reach 266 days from fertilisation (equivalent to 280 days from LMP)."}},
{"@type":"Question","name":"When should I get my first ultrasound in India?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The first scan in India is the dating scan at 8–10 weeks to confirm intrauterine pregnancy, heartbeat, and gestational age. The NT (Nuchal Translucency) scan is done at 11–13+6 weeks for Down syndrome screening. The anomaly scan (Level II) at 18–20 weeks is the most important for structural defects. FOGSI and Indian PNDT Act guidelines recommend that sex determination is illegal."}},
{"@type":"Question","name":"Which government schemes support pregnant women in India?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Key schemes include: PMMVY (Pradhan Mantri Matru Vandana Yojana) — ₹5,000 cash benefit for first live birth; Janani Suraksha Yojana (JSY) — cash for institutional delivery; Janani Shishu Suraksha Karyakram (JSSK) — free ANC, delivery, and postnatal care at government hospitals; PM Surakshit Matritva Abhiyan — free ANC on the 9th of every month."}}
]}
]}
</script>
<style>
*,*::before,*::after{box-sizing:border-box;margin:0;padding:0}
html{scroll-behavior:smooth}
body{font-family:'DM Sans',system-ui,-apple-system,sans-serif;background:#fdf4fb;color:#1a1a2e;overflow-x:hidden;-webkit-text-size-adjust:100%}

/* ── HEADER ── */
.page-header{background:linear-gradient(135deg,#4a0030 0%,#9d174d 50%,#db2777 100%);padding:36px 0 0;position:relative;overflow:hidden}
.page-header::before{content:'';position:absolute;inset:0;background-image:linear-gradient(rgba(255,255,255,0.04) 1px,transparent 1px),linear-gradient(90deg,rgba(255,255,255,0.04) 1px,transparent 1px);background-size:40px 40px}
.page-header::after{content:'';position:absolute;width:500px;height:500px;background:radial-gradient(circle,rgba(244,114,182,0.2) 0%,transparent 70%);top:-100px;right:-50px;pointer-events:none}
.calc-header-inner{max-width:900px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 20px;position:relative;z-index:1}
.breadcrumb{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;font-size:0.72rem;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.45);margin-bottom:14px;flex-wrap:wrap}
.breadcrumb a{color:rgba(255,255,255,0.65);text-decoration:none}
.breadcrumb span{color:rgba(255,255,255,0.3)}
.page-eyebrow{display:inline-flex;align-items:center;background:rgba(255,255,255,0.15);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.25);border-radius:20px;padding:4px 14px;font-size:0.7rem;font-weight:700;color:#fff;letter-spacing:0.06em;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:12px}
h1{font-family:'Fraunces',Georgia,serif;font-size:clamp(1.8rem,5vw,2.8rem);font-weight:900;color:#fff;line-height:1.15;margin-bottom:10px}
h1 em{font-style:italic;color:#f9a8d4}
.page-sub{font-size:0.9rem;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.65);line-height:1.7;max-width:580px;margin-bottom:20px}
.header-badges{display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;padding-bottom:28px}
.hbadge{background:rgba(255,255,255,0.1);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.2);border-radius:20px;padding:3px 10px;font-size:0.67rem;font-weight:600;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.8)}

/* ── MAIN ── */
.main{max-width:900px;margin:0 auto;padding:24px 20px 80px}

/* ── CALC CARD ── */
.calc-card{background:#fff;border:1.5px solid #fce7f3;border-radius:20px;padding:22px 20px;margin-bottom:22px;box-shadow:0 4px 24px rgba(219,39,119,0.08)}
@media(min-width:600px){.calc-card{padding:30px}}

/* Method tabs */
.method-tabs{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr);gap:8px;margin-bottom:20px}
@media(min-width:480px){.method-tabs{grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr)}}
.method-tab{padding:10px 8px;border:2px solid #f3f4f6;border-radius:12px;font-family:inherit;font-size:0.8rem;font-weight:600;cursor:pointer;background:#f9fafb;color:#374151;transition:all 0.2s;touch-action:manipulation;text-align:center}
.method-tab.active{border-color:#db2777;background:#fdf2f8;color:#9d174d}
.method-tab:active{transform:scale(0.97)}

/* Form */
.form-section{display:none}.form-section.active{display:block}
.field-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr;gap:10px;margin-bottom:14px}
@media(min-width:480px){.field-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr}}
.field label{display:block;font-size:0.72rem;font-weight:700;color:#6b7280;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.05em;margin-bottom:5px}
.field input,.field select{width:100%;padding:12px 14px;background:#f9fafb;border:1.5px solid #e5e7eb;border-radius:10px;font-family:inherit;font-size:16px;color:#0d1b2a;outline:none;transition:border-color 0.2s;-webkit-appearance:none;appearance:none}
.field input:focus,.field select:focus{border-color:#db2777;box-shadow:0 0 0 3px rgba(219,39,119,0.1)}
.field .hint{font-size:0.68rem;color:#9ca3af;margin-top:3px}
.error-msg{color:#dc2626;font-size:0.78rem;margin-top:7px;display:none}.error-msg.show{display:block}
.btn-calc{width:100%;padding:14px;border:none;border-radius:12px;color:#fff;font-family:inherit;font-size:1rem;font-weight:700;cursor:pointer;background:linear-gradient(135deg,#db2777,#9d174d);box-shadow:0 4px 16px rgba(219,39,119,0.35);touch-action:manipulation;margin-top:4px}
.btn-calc:active{transform:scale(0.98)}

/* ── RESULTS ── */
.results{display:none;margin-top:20px}.results.show{display:block}
.divider{height:1px;background:#fce7f3;margin:18px 0}

/* Main EDD display */
.edd-banner{background:linear-gradient(135deg,#fdf2f8,#fff5f9);border:2px solid #fbcfe8;border-radius:16px;padding:22px;text-align:center;margin-bottom:16px}
.edd-label{font-size:0.72rem;font-weight:700;color:#9d174d;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.07em;margin-bottom:8px}
.edd-date{font-family:'Fraunces',Georgia,serif;font-size:clamp(1.8rem,6vw,2.8rem);font-weight:900;color:#9d174d;line-height:1;margin-bottom:10px}
.edd-method{font-size:0.75rem;color:#9ca3af;margin-bottom:14px}

/* Stat grid */
.stat-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr);gap:10px;margin-bottom:0}
@media(min-width:480px){.stat-grid{grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr)}}
.sbox{background:#fff;border:1.5px solid #fce7f3;border-radius:12px;padding:12px;text-align:center}
.sbox.hi{background:#fdf2f8;border-color:#f9a8d4}
.sval{font-family:'Fraunces',Georgia,serif;font-size:1.5rem;font-weight:900;color:#db2777;line-height:1;margin-bottom:3px}
.slbl{font-size:0.62rem;font-weight:700;color:#9ca3af;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.05em}

/* Trimester progress bar */
.trimester-bar{background:#f9fafb;border:1.5px solid #fce7f3;border-radius:14px;padding:16px;margin:14px 0}
.tb-top{display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;margin-bottom:8px;font-size:0.78rem;font-weight:700}
.tb-badge{padding:3px 10px;border-radius:20px;font-size:0.7rem;font-weight:700}
.t1{background:#fef3c7;color:#92400e}.t2{background:#d1fae5;color:#065f46}.t3{background:#ede9fe;color:#5b21b6}
.progress-track{background:#f3f4f6;border-radius:20px;height:10px;overflow:hidden}
.progress-fill{height:100%;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(90deg,#f9a8d4,#db2777);transition:width 0.6s ease}
.tb-weeks{display:flex;justify-content:space-between;font-size:0.65rem;color:#9ca3af;margin-top:4px}

/* Next scan card */
.next-scan{background:linear-gradient(135deg,#fdf2f8,#fff);border:1.5px solid #fbcfe8;border-radius:12px;padding:14px 16px;margin:14px 0;display:flex;align-items:flex-start;gap:12px}
.ns-icon{font-size:1.6rem;flex-shrink:0;margin-top:2px}
.ns-title{font-size:0.82rem;font-weight:700;color:#9d174d;margin-bottom:2px}
.ns-desc{font-size:0.76rem;color:#6b7280;line-height:1.5}

/* Weekly timeline */
.timeline-title{font-size:0.72rem;font-weight:700;color:#9d174d;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.06em;margin:16px 0 10px}
.timeline{display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:6px}
.tl-item{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:10px;padding:9px 12px;border-radius:10px;font-size:0.8rem;border:1.5px solid #f3f4f6;background:#f9fafb}
.tl-item.current{background:#fdf2f8;border-color:#fbcfe8;font-weight:700}
.tl-item.done{background:#f0fdf4;border-color:#bbf7d0;opacity:0.8}
.tl-item.upcoming{opacity:0.6}
.tl-week{font-family:'Fraunces',Georgia,serif;font-weight:700;font-size:0.9rem;min-width:40px;color:#db2777}
.tl-item.done .tl-week{color:#10b981}
.tl-dot{width:8px;height:8px;border-radius:50%;background:#d1d5db;flex-shrink:0}
.tl-item.current .tl-dot{background:#db2777}
.tl-item.done .tl-dot{background:#10b981}
.tl-text{flex:1;color:#374151}
.tl-badge{font-size:0.62rem;font-weight:700;padding:2px 7px;border-radius:8px;background:#fce7f3;color:#9d174d;flex-shrink:0}
.tl-item.done .tl-badge{background:#f0fdf4;color:#16a34a}

/* Action row */
.action-row{display:flex;gap:8px;margin-top:14px}
.act-btn{flex:1;padding:11px 8px;border-radius:10px;font-family:inherit;font-size:0.8rem;font-weight:600;cursor:pointer;border:none;touch-action:manipulation;transition:opacity 0.2s}
.act-btn:active{opacity:0.7}
.wa-btn{background:#25d366;color:#fff}
.copy-btn{background:#f3f4f6;border:1.5px solid #e5e7eb;color:#374151}
.reset-btn{width:100%;margin-top:8px;padding:8px;background:transparent;border:1.5px solid #fce7f3;border-radius:10px;color:#9ca3af;font-family:inherit;font-size:0.78rem;cursor:pointer;touch-action:manipulation}
.reset-btn:hover{border-color:#db2777;color:#db2777}

/* ── CONTENT CARDS ── */
.content-card{background:#fff;border:1.5px solid #fce7f3;border-radius:18px;padding:22px 20px;margin-bottom:18px}
@media(min-width:600px){.content-card{padding:28px}}
.content-card h2{font-family:'Fraunces',Georgia,serif;font-size:1.3rem;font-weight:900;color:#0d1b2a;margin-bottom:14px;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px}
.content-card h3{font-size:0.95rem;font-weight:700;color:#db2777;margin:18px 0 8px}
.content-card p{font-size:0.87rem;color:#4b5563;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:10px}
.content-card ul,.content-card ol{list-style:none;padding:0;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:6px;margin-bottom:10px}
.content-card li{font-size:0.85rem;color:#4b5563;padding-left:14px;position:relative;line-height:1.6}
.content-card li::before{content:'→';position:absolute;left:0;color:#db2777;font-size:0.78rem}
.content-card ol li::before{content:counter(item) '.';counter-increment:item;font-weight:700;color:#db2777}
.content-card ol{counter-reset:item}

/* Scan table */
.scan-table{width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;font-size:0.8rem;margin:12px 0;overflow-x:auto;display:block}
@media(min-width:600px){.scan-table{display:table}}
.scan-table th{background:#fdf2f8;color:#9d174d;font-weight:700;padding:8px 10px;text-align:left;font-size:0.68rem;text-transform:uppercase;border-bottom:2px solid #fbcfe8}
.scan-table td{padding:9px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #fdf2f8;color:#374151;vertical-align:top}
.scan-table tr:hover td{background:#fdf2f8}
.scan-tag{display:inline-block;font-size:0.62rem;font-weight:700;padding:2px 7px;border-radius:8px;margin-left:4px}
.tag-must{background:#fef2f2;color:#dc2626;border:1px solid #fecaca}
.tag-legal{background:#fffbeb;color:#d97706;border:1px solid #fde68a}

/* Highlight box */
.highlight-box{background:#fefce8;border:1.5px solid #fef08a;border-radius:12px;padding:14px 16px;font-size:0.84rem;color:#854d0e;line-height:1.7;margin:12px 0}
.alert-box{background:#fef2f2;border:1.5px solid #fecaca;border-radius:12px;padding:14px 16px;font-size:0.84rem;color:#991b1b;line-height:1.7;margin:12px 0}

/* Gov schemes */
.scheme-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr;gap:10px;margin:12px 0}
@media(min-width:480px){.scheme-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr}}
.scheme-card{background:#fdf2f8;border:1.5px solid #fbcfe8;border-radius:12px;padding:14px}
.sc-title{font-size:0.85rem;font-weight:700;color:#9d174d;margin-bottom:4px}
.sc-amt{font-family:'Fraunces',Georgia,serif;font-size:1.2rem;font-weight:900;color:#db2777;margin-bottom:4px}
.sc-desc{font-size:0.75rem;color:#6b7280;line-height:1.5}

/* FAQ */
.faq-item{border-bottom:1px solid #fce7f3;padding:14px 0}.faq-item:last-child{border-bottom:none}
.faq-q{font-size:0.9rem;font-weight:600;color:#0d1b2a;cursor:pointer;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:flex-start;gap:10px;user-select:none;touch-action:manipulation}
.faq-q::after{content:'＋';color:#db2777;font-size:1rem;flex-shrink:0;transition:transform 0.2s}
.faq-item.open .faq-q::after{transform:rotate(45deg)}
.faq-a{max-height:0;overflow:hidden;transition:max-height 0.3s ease;font-size:0.84rem;color:#4b5563;line-height:1.75}
.faq-item.open .faq-a{max-height:400px;padding-top:8px}

/* Related grid */
.related-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:10px}
@media(min-width:600px){.related-grid{grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr)}}
.related-card{background:#fdf2f8;border:1.5px solid #fce7f3;border-radius:11px;padding:12px;text-decoration:none;color:inherit;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;touch-action:manipulation;transition:all 0.15s}
.related-card:active,.related-card:hover{border-color:#db2777}
.rc-icon{font-size:1.2rem;flex-shrink:0}
.rc-title{font-size:0.79rem;font-weight:700;color:#0d1b2a;margin-bottom:1px}
.rc-desc{font-size:0.66rem;color:#9ca3af}
.disclaimer{background:#fffbeb;border:1.5px solid #fde68a;border-radius:11px;padding:12px;font-size:0.74rem;color:#78350f;line-height:1.6;margin-top:16px}
</style>
<style>
/* ── MOBILE NAV FIX ── prevents shared-nav overlay on page header */
.page-header { margin-top: 0; position: relative; z-index: 1; }
.calc-header-inner { position: relative; z-index: 2; }
.site-header { z-index: 1000 !important; }
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .site-nav.open { z-index: 999 !important; }
  /* Ensure page content sits below sticky nav */
  .page-header { padding-top: 0 !important; }
}
</style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="page-header">
  <div class="calc-header-inner">
    <nav class="breadcrumb"><a href="/">Home</a><span>›</span><a href="/medical-calculators/">Calculators</a><span>›</span><span>Due Date</span></nav>
    <div class="page-eyebrow">🤰 Obstetrics · India Edition</div>
    <h1>Pregnancy Due Date<br><em>Calculator</em></h1>
    <p class="page-sub">Calculate your EDD from LMP, IVF transfer, or ultrasound. See your trimester progress, upcoming scans, and week-by-week milestones.</p>
    <div class="header-badges">
      <span class="hbadge">✓ LMP · IVF · Ultrasound · Conception</span>
      <span class="hbadge">✓ Trimester Progress</span>
      <span class="hbadge">✓ Indian Scan Schedule</span>
      <span class="hbadge">✓ FOGSI-Aligned</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<main class="main">
  <div class="calc-card">
    <!-- Method Tabs -->
    <div class="method-tabs">
      <button class="method-tab active" onclick="switchMethod(event,'lmp')">📅 LMP</button>
      <button class="method-tab" onclick="switchMethod(event,'ultrasound')">🔊 Ultrasound</button>
      <button class="method-tab" onclick="switchMethod(event,'ivf')">🧪 IVF / FET</button>
      <button class="method-tab" onclick="switchMethod(event,'conception')">🌸 Conception</button>
    </div>

    <!-- LMP -->
    <div id="form-lmp" class="form-section active">
      <div class="field-grid">
        <div class="field">
          <label>First Day of Last Period (LMP)</label>
          <input type="date" id="lmp-date" inputmode="none"/>
          <div class="hint">The first day of your last menstrual period</div>
        </div>
        <div class="field">
          <label>Cycle Length</label>
          <select id="cycle-length">
            <option value="21">21 days (short)</option>
            <option value="24">24 days</option>
            <option value="25">25 days</option>
            <option value="26">26 days</option>
            <option value="27">27 days</option>
            <option value="28" selected>28 days (standard)</option>
            <option value="29">29 days</option>
            <option value="30">30 days</option>
            <option value="31">31 days</option>
            <option value="32">32 days</option>
            <option value="33">33 days</option>
            <option value="34">34 days</option>
            <option value="35">35 days</option>
            <option value="38">38 days</option>
            <option value="40">40 days (long)</option>
            <option value="45">45 days (very long)</option>
          </select>
          <div class="hint">Naegele's rule adjusted for cycle length</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Ultrasound -->
    <div id="form-ultrasound" class="form-section">
      <div class="field-grid">
        <div class="field">
          <label>Scan Date</label>
          <input type="date" id="us-date" inputmode="none"/>
        </div>
        <div class="field">
          <label>Gestational Age at Scan</label>
          <select id="us-weeks-sel">
            <option value="">Select weeks...</option>
            <option value="6">6 weeks</option>
            <option value="7">7 weeks</option>
            <option value="8">8 weeks</option>
            <option value="9">9 weeks</option>
            <option value="10">10 weeks</option>
            <option value="11">11 weeks</option>
            <option value="12">12 weeks (NT scan)</option>
            <option value="13">13 weeks</option>
            <option value="14">14 weeks</option>
            <option value="18">18 weeks</option>
            <option value="19">19 weeks</option>
            <option value="20">20 weeks (anomaly)</option>
          </select>
          <div class="hint">Gestational age confirmed by radiologist/obstetrician</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="highlight-box" style="margin-top:0">💡 Early scan (7–13 weeks, CRL measurement) is the most accurate dating method. If the ultrasound date differs from LMP by &gt;7 days, obstetricians typically use the ultrasound date.</div>
    </div>

    <!-- IVF -->
    <div id="form-ivf" class="form-section">
      <div class="field-grid">
        <div class="field">
          <label>Embryo Transfer Date</label>
          <input type="date" id="ivf-date" inputmode="none"/>
        </div>
        <div class="field">
          <label>Embryo Age at Transfer</label>
          <select id="ivf-type">
            <option value="5">Day 5 — Blastocyst (+261 days)</option>
            <option value="3">Day 3 — Cleavage (+263 days)</option>
            <option value="2">Day 2 — Early cleavage (+264 days)</option>
          </select>
          <div class="hint">Days from fertilisation to transfer</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="highlight-box" style="margin-top:0">💡 IVF EDD = Transfer Date + (266 − embryo age) days. Day 5 blastocysts add 261 days; Day 3 add 263 days.</div>
    </div>

    <!-- Conception -->
    <div id="form-conception" class="form-section">
      <div class="field-grid">
        <div class="field">
          <label>Conception Date</label>
          <input type="date" id="conception-date" inputmode="none"/>
          <div class="hint">Date of unprotected intercourse / ovulation</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="highlight-box" style="margin-top:0">💡 EDD = Conception Date + 266 days (38 weeks from conception = 40 weeks from LMP).</div>
    </div>

    <div class="error-msg" id="error-msg"></div>
    <button class="btn-calc" onclick="calculate()">Calculate Due Date →</button>

    <!-- RESULTS -->
    <div class="results" id="results">
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <div class="edd-banner">
        <div class="edd-label">Estimated Due Date (EDD)</div>
        <div class="edd-date" id="edd-display">—</div>
        <div class="edd-method" id="edd-method">—</div>
        <div class="stat-grid">
          <div class="sbox hi"><div class="sval" id="r-week">—</div><div class="slbl">Weeks</div></div>
          <div class="sbox hi"><div class="sval" id="r-days">—</div><div class="slbl">Days to go</div></div>
          <div class="sbox"><div class="sval" id="r-tri">—</div><div class="slbl">Trimester</div></div>
          <div class="sbox"><div class="sval" id="r-size">—</div><div class="slbl">Baby size</div></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Trimester Progress -->
      <div class="trimester-bar">
        <div class="tb-top">
          <span id="tri-name">—</span>
          <span class="tb-badge" id="tri-badge"></span>
        </div>
        <div class="progress-track">
          <div class="progress-fill" id="progress-fill" style="width:0%"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="tb-weeks">
          <span>Week 1</span><span>Week 13</span><span>Week 27</span><span>Week 40</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Next Upcoming Scan -->
      <div class="next-scan" id="next-scan" style="display:none">
        <div class="ns-icon" id="ns-icon">🔬</div>
        <div>
          <div class="ns-title" id="ns-title">—</div>
          <div class="ns-desc" id="ns-desc">—</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Weekly Milestones Timeline -->
      <div class="timeline-title">📅 Your Antenatal Timeline</div>
      <div class="timeline" id="timeline"></div>

      <div class="action-row">
        <button class="act-btn wa-btn" onclick="shareWA()">📲 WhatsApp</button>
        <button class="act-btn copy-btn" onclick="copyResult()">📋 Copy</button>
      </div>
      <button class="reset-btn" onclick="resetCalc()">↺ Reset</button>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- SCAN SCHEDULE -->
  <div class="content-card">
    <h2>🔬 Indian Antenatal Scan Schedule</h2>
    <table class="scan-table">
      <thead><tr><th>Week</th><th>Scan / Test</th><th>Purpose</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><strong>6–8</strong></td><td>Early viability scan</td><td>Confirm intrauterine pregnancy, heartbeat, rule out ectopic. Not always routine if asymptomatic</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>8–10</strong></td><td>Dating scan</td><td>Confirm gestational age by CRL (crown-rump length). Correct EDD if needed</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>11–13+6</strong></td><td>NT scan + Dual Marker <span class="scan-tag tag-must">Recommended</span></td><td>Nuchal translucency for Down syndrome risk. Combined with PAPP-A and β-hCG blood test</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>18–20</strong></td><td>Anomaly scan (Level II / TIFFA) <span class="scan-tag tag-must">Most Important</span></td><td>Detailed fetal anatomy — heart, brain, spine, limbs, kidneys. Detects >80% of structural anomalies</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>24–28</strong></td><td>75g OGTT (gestational diabetes) <span class="scan-tag tag-must">India</span></td><td>GDM prevalence is very high in Indian women (16–17%). DIPSI protocol: 75g glucose, 2h blood sugar ≥140 mg/dL = GDM</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>28</strong></td><td>Anti-D injection</td><td>For Rh-negative mothers. Prevents Rh incompatibility in subsequent pregnancies</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>30–32</strong></td><td>Growth scan + Colour Doppler</td><td>Estimate fetal weight, liquor, placental position. Uterine and umbilical artery Doppler for IUGR screening</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>36</strong></td><td>Group B Streptococcus (GBS) swab</td><td>Recommended in tertiary centres. If positive, IV antibiotics in labour to prevent neonatal sepsis</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>36–40</strong></td><td>Final growth scan / CTG</td><td>Fetal wellbeing, presentation (vertex/breech), decide delivery plan</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <div class="alert-box">⚠️ <strong>PC-PNDT Act:</strong> Sex determination of the foetus is illegal in India under the PC-PNDT Act 1994. All registered ultrasound centres must maintain Form F for every scan. Violations carry imprisonment up to 3 years.</div>
  </div>

  <!-- GOVERNMENT SCHEMES -->
  <div class="content-card">
    <h2>🏛️ Government Schemes for Pregnant Women in India</h2>
    <div class="scheme-grid">
      <div class="scheme-card">
        <div class="sc-title">PMMVY</div>
        <div class="sc-amt">₹5,000</div>
        <div class="sc-desc">Pradhan Mantri Matru Vandana Yojana — cash benefit for first live birth in 3 instalments. Apply at Anganwadi / ASHA worker within 270 days of conception</div>
      </div>
      <div class="scheme-card">
        <div class="sc-title">Janani Suraksha Yojana (JSY)</div>
        <div class="sc-amt">₹1,400–1,600</div>
        <div class="sc-desc">Cash incentive for institutional delivery in government hospitals for BPL mothers. Higher amount for rural areas. Applied through ANM/ASHA</div>
      </div>
      <div class="scheme-card">
        <div class="sc-title">JSSK</div>
        <div class="sc-amt">Free</div>
        <div class="sc-desc">Janani Shishu Suraksha Karyakram — free ANC, delivery, C-section, postnatal care, newborn care, and medicines at all government facilities. No out-of-pocket expenses</div>
      </div>
      <div class="scheme-card">
        <div class="sc-title">PM-SURAKSHA</div>
        <div class="sc-amt">Free ANC</div>
        <div class="sc-desc">PM Surakshit Matritva Abhiyan — free comprehensive ANC on the 9th of every month at government facilities. Includes blood tests, iron, calcium, and doctor consultation</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p style="margin-top:10px">Documents needed: Aadhaar card, MCP (Mother &amp; Child Protection) card, BPL card (if applicable), bank account details. Register through your nearest Anganwadi centre or ANM at the sub-centre.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- NUTRITIONAL GUIDE -->
  <div class="content-card">
    <h2>🥗 Indian Pregnancy Nutrition Guide</h2>
    <h3>First Trimester (Weeks 1–13)</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Folic acid 5 mg/day:</strong> Neural tube defect prevention — start before conception, continue till 12 weeks. Available free at government hospitals</li>
      <li><strong>Iron + Folic acid (IFA):</strong> Start from first trimester — ICMR recommends 180 mg elemental iron + 500 µg folic acid daily for anaemia prevention</li>
      <li><strong>Ginger tea / jeera water:</strong> Safe home remedies for nausea. Small frequent meals. Avoid raw papaya, pineapple, sesame seeds in large amounts</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>Second Trimester (Weeks 14–27)</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Calcium 1000–1200 mg/day:</strong> Essential for fetal bone formation. Sources: milk, curd, paneer, ragi, til (sesame). Calcium carbonate supplements commonly prescribed in India</li>
      <li><strong>Protein 70–100 g/day:</strong> Dal, rajma, chana, eggs, milk, paneer. Very high need — most Indian women are protein-deficient in pregnancy</li>
      <li><strong>OGTT at 24–28 weeks:</strong> Indian women have 4× higher risk of GDM. DIPSI protocol: 75g glucose (non-fasting), 2h BS ≥140 mg/dL = GDM. Requires immediate dietary modification</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>Third Trimester (Weeks 28–40)</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Iron absorption:</strong> Take iron tablets at bedtime, not with milk or tea. Vitamin C (amla, lemon) improves absorption. Common side effect: dark stools (normal)</li>
      <li><strong>Omega-3 (DHA):</strong> Walnuts, flaxseeds, fatty fish (safe 2x/week). Important for fetal brain development. Many obstetricians prescribe DHA supplements from second trimester</li>
      <li><strong>Avoid:</strong> Alcohol completely, raw/undercooked meat, unpasteurised milk, excess Vitamin A (liver, cod liver oil), caffeine &gt;200 mg/day (&lt;2 cups of tea)</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <!-- LABOUR SIGNS -->
  <div class="content-card">
    <h2>🚑 Signs of Labour — When to Go to Hospital</h2>
    <div class="alert-box">🚨 <strong>Go to hospital immediately</strong> if: heavy vaginal bleeding, severe headache + visual disturbance (pre-eclampsia), no fetal movement for &gt;2 hours, cord prolapse, or severe abdominal pain at any gestation.</div>
    <h3>True Labour Signs (after 37 weeks)</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Regular contractions:</strong> Every 5 minutes, lasting 60 seconds, for 1 hour — the "5-1-1 rule". Contractions start in the back and radiate to the front. Getting stronger, longer, closer together</li>
      <li><strong>Rupture of membranes (water breaking):</strong> Sudden gush or continuous trickle of clear/pale yellow fluid. Go to hospital within 1–2 hours even without contractions — risk of cord prolapse and infection after 18 hours</li>
      <li><strong>Show (bloody mucus plug):</strong> Passage of mucus mixed with blood — labour usually begins within 24–48 hours. Not an emergency, but alert your doctor</li>
      <li><strong>Reduced fetal movements:</strong> Less than 10 movements in 2 hours at any point in third trimester — go to hospital for CTG monitoring immediately</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>Kick Count (After 28 Weeks)</h3>
    <p>Count kicks daily — aim for 10 movements within 2 hours after a meal when the baby is usually most active. Keep a kick count diary. This is the most important self-monitoring tool in the third trimester and can detect fetal distress early.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <div class="content-card">
    <h2>❓ Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div id="faq-container"></div>
  </div>

  <!-- RELATED -->
  <div class="content-card">
    <h2>Related Calculators</h2>
    <div class="related-grid">
      <a href="/medical-calculators/obs-calc" class="related-card"><span class="rc-icon">🏥</span><div><div class="rc-title">ObsCalc Suite</div><div class="rc-desc">Bishop, EFW, VBAC</div></div></a>
      <a href="/medical-calculators/growth-chart" class="related-card"><span class="rc-icon">📈</span><div><div class="rc-title">Growth Chart</div><div class="rc-desc">WHO/IAP Z-scores</div></div></a>
      <a href="/medical-calculators/neonatal-jaundice" class="related-card"><span class="rc-icon">🌟</span><div><div class="rc-title">Neonatal Jaundice</div><div class="rc-desc">Phototherapy thresholds</div></div></a>
      <a href="/medical-calculators/apgar-score" class="related-card"><span class="rc-icon">👶</span><div><div class="rc-title">APGAR Score</div><div class="rc-desc">Newborn assessment</div></div></a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="disclaimer"><strong>⚠ Medical Disclaimer:</strong> This calculator provides an estimated due date only. Clinical decisions including EDD confirmation, gestational age assessment, and pregnancy management must be made by a registered obstetrician or gynaecologist. All calculations follow FOGSI and WHO guidelines.</div>
</main>


<script>
let lastResult=null;let currentEDD=null;let currentWeeks=0;

// ── ANTENATAL MILESTONES ──
const MILESTONES=[
  {w:4,text:'Missed period — do a pregnancy test (urine hCG)',key:'confirm'},
  {w:6,text:'Heartbeat visible on transvaginal scan (TVS)',key:'tvs'},
  {w:8,text:'Book appointment — first ANC visit. Blood group, CBC, blood sugar, TSH, VDRL',key:'anc1'},
  {w:10,text:'Dating scan — confirm gestational age by CRL',key:'dating'},
  {w:12,text:'NT scan + Dual Marker (Down syndrome screening)',key:'nt'},
  {w:13,text:'End of first trimester 🎉 Risk of miscarriage drops significantly',key:'t1end'},
  {w:16,text:'Quadruple marker screen (if NT scan not done)',key:'quad'},
  {w:18,text:'Start feeling fetal movements (quickening)',key:'quicken'},
  {w:20,text:'Anomaly scan (Level II / TIFFA) — most important scan',key:'anom'},
  {w:24,text:'75g OGTT — gestational diabetes screening (DIPSI protocol)',key:'ogtt'},
  {w:27,text:'End of second trimester',key:'t2end'},
  {w:28,text:'Anti-D injection if Rh-negative. CBC + iron check',key:'antid'},
  {w:30,text:'Growth scan + Colour Doppler',key:'growth'},
  {w:32,text:'Discuss birth plan with obstetrician',key:'birthplan'},
  {w:34,text:'Confirm fetal presentation (vertex/breech)',key:'presentation'},
  {w:36,text:'Group B Strep swab. Weekly CTG if high-risk',key:'gbs'},
  {w:37,text:'Baby is TERM 🎉 Pack your hospital bag',key:'term'},
  {w:38,text:'Final check — fetal wellbeing, growth, liquor',key:'final'},
  {w:40,text:'Due Date! If no labour, NST/BPP every 2–3 days',key:'edd'},
  {w:41,text:'Post-dates — induction usually planned at 41 weeks in India',key:'postdate'},
];

// Next upcoming scan details
const SCANS=[
  {minW:0,maxW:8,title:'Dating Scan (8–10 weeks)',desc:'Book your first obstetric scan. Will confirm intrauterine pregnancy, heartbeat (CRL), and correct EDD if needed.',icon:'🔬'},
  {minW:8,maxW:12,title:'NT Scan + Dual Marker (11–13 weeks)',desc:'Nuchal translucency for Down syndrome risk screening. Combined with PAPP-A and β-hCG blood test. Book now.',icon:'🧬'},
  {minW:12,maxW:18,title:'Anomaly Scan / TIFFA (18–20 weeks)',desc:'Most important scan — detailed head-to-toe anatomy check. Book at a PNDT-registered centre.',icon:'🔬'},
  {minW:18,maxW:24,title:'75g OGTT — Gestational Diabetes (24–28 weeks)',desc:'DIPSI protocol — 75g oral glucose, 2-hour blood sugar. Indian women have very high GDM risk.',icon:'🩸'},
  {minW:24,maxW:30,title:'Growth Scan + Doppler (30–32 weeks)',desc:'Estimate fetal weight, liquor, placental position. Uterine and umbilical artery Doppler.',icon:'📊'},
  {minW:30,maxW:36,title:'Final Growth Scan (36–40 weeks)',desc:'Confirm fetal presentation, wellbeing, and delivery planning. CTG if high-risk.',icon:'📋'},
  {minW:36,maxW:42,title:'CTG / Biophysical Profile',desc:'Non-stress test (NST/CTG) for fetal wellbeing monitoring approaching term.',icon:'❤️'},
];

const FRUIT_SIZE=[
  [4,'Poppy seed'],[5,'Sesame seed'],[6,'Pea'],[7,'Blueberry'],[8,'Raspberry'],
  [9,'Cherry (Cher)'],[10,'Strawberry'],[11,'Lime'],[12,'Lemon'],[13,'Lemon'],
  [14,'Orange'],[15,'Mandarin'],[16,'Apple'],[17,'Pear'],[18,'Bell pepper'],
  [19,'Mango'],[20,'Banana'],[22,'Papaya / Papita'],[24,'Corn cob'],[26,'Cucumber'],
  [28,'Kairi (raw mango)'],[30,'Cabbage'],[32,'Squash'],[34,'Pineapple'],[36,'Honeydew'],
  [38,'Watermelon / Tarbooz'],[40,'Pumpkin / Kaddu'],
];

function getFruitSize(w){
  for(let i=FRUIT_SIZE.length-1;i>=0;i--){if(w>=FRUIT_SIZE[i][0])return FRUIT_SIZE[i][1];}
  return 'Tiny seed';
}

function switchMethod(event,m){
  document.querySelectorAll('.method-tab').forEach(t=>t.classList.remove('active'));
  event.currentTarget.classList.add('active');
  document.querySelectorAll('.form-section').forEach(s=>s.classList.remove('active'));
  document.getElementById('form-'+m).classList.add('active');
}

function calculate(){
  const errEl=document.getElementById('error-msg');errEl.className='error-msg';
  const today=new Date();today.setHours(0,0,0,0);
  let edd=null;let methodLabel='';
  const m=document.querySelector('.method-tab.active').textContent.trim().replace(/[^\w ]/g,'').trim();

  if(m.includes('LMP')||document.getElementById('form-lmp').classList.contains('active')){
    const val=document.getElementById('lmp-date').value;
    if(!val){errEl.textContent='Please select your LMP date.';errEl.className='error-msg show';return}
    const lmp=new Date(val);lmp.setHours(0,0,0,0);
    if(lmp>today){errEl.textContent='LMP cannot be in the future.';errEl.className='error-msg show';return}
    const cycle=parseInt(document.getElementById('cycle-length').value)||28;
    const adjust=cycle-28;// days offset from standard 28-day cycle
    edd=new Date(lmp.getTime()+(280+adjust)*864e5);
    methodLabel='From LMP (Naegele\'s Rule, '+cycle+'-day cycle)';
    if(typeof umami!=='undefined')umami.track('edd_lmp',{cycle});
  } else if(document.getElementById('form-ultrasound').classList.contains('active')){
    const val=document.getElementById('us-date').value;
    const w=parseInt(document.getElementById('us-weeks-sel').value);
    if(!val){errEl.textContent='Please select scan date.';errEl.className='error-msg show';return}
    if(!w){errEl.textContent='Please select gestational age at scan.';errEl.className='error-msg show';return}
    const dt=new Date(val);dt.setHours(0,0,0,0);
    edd=new Date(dt.getTime()+(40-w)*7*864e5);
    methodLabel='From Ultrasound ('+w+' weeks at scan)';
    if(typeof umami!=='undefined')umami.track('edd_us',{weeks:w});
  } else if(document.getElementById('form-ivf').classList.contains('active')){
    const val=document.getElementById('ivf-date').value;
    const embryoAge=parseInt(document.getElementById('ivf-type').value);
    if(!val){errEl.textContent='Please select transfer date.';errEl.className='error-msg show';return}
    const dt=new Date(val);dt.setHours(0,0,0,0);
    const daysToAdd=266-embryoAge;
    edd=new Date(dt.getTime()+daysToAdd*864e5);
    const typeLabel=embryoAge===5?'Day 5 Blastocyst':embryoAge===3?'Day 3 Embryo':'Day 2 Embryo';
    methodLabel='From IVF Transfer ('+typeLabel+')';
    if(typeof umami!=='undefined')umami.track('edd_ivf',{embryoAge});
  } else {
    const val=document.getElementById('conception-date').value;
    if(!val){errEl.textContent='Please select conception date.';errEl.className='error-msg show';return}
    const dt=new Date(val);dt.setHours(0,0,0,0);
    edd=new Date(dt.getTime()+266*864e5);
    methodLabel='From Conception Date';
    if(typeof umami!=='undefined')umami.track('edd_conception');
  }

  currentEDD=edd;
  const diff=edd-today;
  const daysLeft=Math.ceil(diff/864e5);
  // Gestational age in weeks (from LMP equivalent)
  const lmpEquiv=new Date(edd.getTime()-280*864e5);
  const daysPregnant=Math.floor((today-lmpEquiv)/864e5);
  const weeksPreg=Math.floor(daysPregnant/7);
  const daysExtra=daysPregnant%7;
  currentWeeks=weeksPreg;

  // Trimester
  let trimLabel,trimBadge,triBadgeCls,triName;
  if(weeksPreg<=13){trimLabel='1st Trimester';trimBadge='Weeks 1–13';triBadgeCls='t1';triName='First Trimester'}
  else if(weeksPreg<=27){trimLabel='2nd Trimester';trimBadge='Weeks 14–27';triBadgeCls='t2';triName='Second Trimester'}
  else{trimLabel='3rd Trimester';trimBadge='Weeks 28–40';triBadgeCls='t3';triName='Third Trimester'}

  const progressPct=Math.min(Math.max((weeksPreg/40)*100,2),100);

  // Display
  document.getElementById('edd-display').textContent=edd.toLocaleDateString('en-IN',{weekday:'long',day:'numeric',month:'long',year:'numeric'});
  document.getElementById('edd-method').textContent=methodLabel;
  document.getElementById('r-week').textContent=weeksPreg+'w '+daysExtra+'d';
  document.getElementById('r-days').textContent=daysLeft>0?daysLeft:'Due!';
  document.getElementById('r-tri').textContent=trimLabel.replace(' Trimester','').replace('1st','1st').replace('2nd','2nd').replace('3rd','3rd');
  document.getElementById('r-size').textContent=getFruitSize(weeksPreg);
  document.getElementById('tri-name').textContent=triName+' ('+weeksPreg+'w '+daysExtra+'d)';
  const badge=document.getElementById('tri-badge');badge.textContent=trimBadge;badge.className='tb-badge '+triBadgeCls;
  document.getElementById('progress-fill').style.width=progressPct+'%';

  // Next scan
  const nextScan=SCANS.find(s=>weeksPreg>=s.minW&&weeksPreg<s.maxW);
  if(nextScan){
    document.getElementById('next-scan').style.display='flex';
    document.getElementById('ns-icon').textContent=nextScan.icon;
    document.getElementById('ns-title').textContent='Next: '+nextScan.title;
    document.getElementById('ns-desc').textContent=nextScan.desc;
  } else {document.getElementById('next-scan').style.display='none';}

  // Timeline
  buildTimeline(weeksPreg,edd,lmpEquiv);

  lastResult=`🤰 Pregnancy Due Date Calculator\nEDD: ${edd.toLocaleDateString('en-IN',{day:'numeric',month:'long',year:'numeric'})}\nMethod: ${methodLabel}\nCurrently: ${weeksPreg} weeks ${daysExtra} days pregnant\nTrimester: ${trimLabel}\nDays to go: ${daysLeft>0?daysLeft:0}\nBaby size: ${getFruitSize(weeksPreg)}\n\nCalculated at rxmedcalc.com/medical-calculators/due-date`;

  document.getElementById('results').className='results show';
  document.getElementById('results').scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth',block:'nearest'});
}

function buildTimeline(currentWeek,edd,lmpEquiv){
  const show=MILESTONES.filter(m=>m.w>=currentWeek-2&&m.w<=Math.min(currentWeek+8,42));
  const container=document.getElementById('timeline');
  container.innerHTML=show.map(m=>{
    const mDate=new Date(lmpEquiv.getTime()+m.w*7*864e5);
    const dateStr=mDate.toLocaleDateString('en-IN',{day:'numeric',month:'short'});
    let cls='tl-item';
    if(m.w<currentWeek)cls+=' done';
    else if(m.w===currentWeek)cls+=' current';
    else cls+=' upcoming';
    return `<div class="${cls}">
      <div class="tl-week">W${m.w}</div>
      <div class="tl-dot"></div>
      <div class="tl-text">${m.text}</div>
      <div class="tl-badge">${dateStr}</div>
    </div>`;
  }).join('');
}

function shareWA(){if(!lastResult)return;window.open('https://wa.me/?text='+encodeURIComponent(lastResult),'_blank')}
function copyResult(){if(!lastResult)return;navigator.clipboard.writeText(lastResult).then(()=>{const b=document.querySelector('.copy-btn');b.textContent='✓ Copied!';setTimeout(()=>{b.textContent='📋 Copy'},2000)})}
function resetCalc(){
  ['lmp-date','us-date','ivf-date','conception-date'].forEach(id=>{const el=document.getElementById(id);if(el)el.value=''});
  document.getElementById('us-weeks-sel').value='';
  document.getElementById('results').className='results';
  document.getElementById('error-msg').className='error-msg';
  lastResult=null;currentEDD=null;
}

// FAQ
const faqs=[
  ['How is the due date calculated from LMP?','Using Naegele\'s Rule: add 280 days (40 weeks) to the first day of the Last Menstrual Period (LMP), adjusted for cycle length. Our calculator adjusts for any cycle length from 21 to 45 days — longer cycles push the EDD later, shorter cycles bring it forward.'],
  ['How accurate is ultrasound dating vs LMP?','An early ultrasound measuring the Crown-Rump Length (CRL) between 7–13 weeks is accurate to ±5–7 days and is the gold standard. LMP is accurate to ±2 weeks. If they differ by more than 7 days, your obstetrician will typically use the ultrasound date as the official EDD.'],
  ['What is the due date calculation for IVF Day 5 transfer?','For a Day 5 blastocyst transfer: EDD = Transfer Date + 261 days. For Day 3: EDD = Transfer Date + 263 days. The formula is: EDD = Transfer Date + (266 − embryo age at transfer). This is because embryos are 266 days from fertilisation to due date.'],
  ['When should I get my first antenatal check in India?','Ideally within the first 8–10 weeks. Your first ANC visit includes blood tests (CBC, blood group and Rh type, blood sugar, TSH, VDRL/RPR, HIV, Hepatitis B), urine examination, blood pressure, weight, and booking scan. Register for MCP (Mother and Child Protection) card and government schemes at your nearest PHC or ANM.'],
  ['What is the DIPSI protocol for gestational diabetes screening?','DIPSI (Diabetic Pregnancy Study Group India): Give 75g oral glucose at any time of day (non-fasting). Blood sugar measured at 2 hours. A value ≥140 mg/dL = GDM. This simpler test is preferred in India because Indian women have very high GDM risk (16–17%) and the test can be done without overnight fasting.'],
  ['Can the due date change after an early ultrasound?','Yes. If your ultrasound-based GA differs from your LMP-based GA by more than 7 days (1st trimester) or 14 days (2nd trimester), the EDD is usually revised. Multiple revisions are not recommended — the 1st trimester scan is most accurate and should generally be the final EDD.'],
  ['Is it safe to travel during pregnancy?','Best time to travel is the second trimester (14–28 weeks). Avoid long-haul travel after 36 weeks. Always carry your maternity notes/MCP card and emergency contacts. On flights, walk every 2 hours to prevent DVT, wear compression stockings. Check airline policies (most allow travel up to 36 weeks with a letter).'],
  ['What vaccines are recommended during pregnancy in India?','Tetanus toxoid (Td): 2 doses in first pregnancy (at 16–24 weeks and 4 weeks later) or 1 booster in subsequent. Influenza vaccine: recommended. COVID vaccine: recommended as per current NHP guidelines. All given free at government antenatal clinics.'],
];
document.getElementById('faq-container').innerHTML=faqs.map((f,i)=>`<div class="faq-item" id="faq-${i}"><div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(${i})" tabindex="0">${f[0]}</div><div class="faq-a">${f[1]}</div></div>`).join('');
function toggleFaq(i){const item=document.getElementById('faq-'+i);const o=item.classList.contains('open');document.querySelectorAll('.faq-item').forEach(e=>e.classList.remove('open'));if(!o)item.classList.add('open')}
</script>
<script src="/assets/shared-nav.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
